<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=746637" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=746637</a>
<br />

<br />

<br />
Only 6 mana more. The shoulder item before was augumented and hat +11 INT but now I am at +7INT, some mana and +5DEX which I guess is better. Found the pauldron for 3k on the bazaar and thought not worth it. Right after that someone was auctioning on POK for 1.5k and I grabbed it.
<br />

<br />
Next update was my staff. Like the look on the new one better. Staff cost 8.5k. Then went to upgrade range and I choose focus effect over mana/int. The sword cost me 5k. Last update was the horse then. I went to get the black one cause it looked nicer than the white one in the stable.
<br />
About 30min after buying it I nearly feel of a bridge in Dulak while trying to get the Soulstripper for a friend. I didnt fall and 3 spawn was the named with PH. I felt lucky and gave hammer to cleric. 
<br />
After that I did a ldon where I couldnt use horse of course but then I decided at around 1.30am I could go to GD and do some faction. Well let me just tell you horsehead got me killed. I think it neads alot of getting used to and I find myself changing perspective a whole lot more. Once playing in 3rd person everything seems rather ok.
<br />
What I did notice though is what difference it means. I never thought it was that much mana. 
<br />

<br />
thanks again for all the replies before.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.na-la.de/sig.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
